&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Inpatient Medicine Physiotherapy - Technical Instructor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Band 3 - Full Time - 37.5 hours&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an existing Physiotherapy Assistant to become a Technical Instructor in Medicine. This post will be based on the medical wards but may be required to work flexibly across teams. An interest in the medical and older patient group as well as an awareness of dementia and aging/ multi pathologies would be beneficial. You will get the opportunity to work on all wards within the medical team and, after completing competency training, manage your own caseload of patients as well as supporting qualified staff. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Candidates require excellent written and spoken English as well as excellent team working skills, adaptability and flexibility. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; There is a requirement for flexible working as the service operates over 7 days on a rostered pattern.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
